column5: I have to pick a buddy up in the twin cities this year. what is the best route to take to get up to fort frances Also, how is the cell coverage? have to meet up with another party someplace along the way?

Assume your refering to Twin Cities as Minn/St.Paul, correct? (forgive me, I'm an Okie) If so, we take I-35 north to Exit 237 at Cloquet which puts you on SH 33. Stay on SH 33 (north) and it will run right into 53 which in turn will take you straight into International Falls where we cross the border into Ft. Frances. Hope thats what you were looking for.
Follow Hawker's route. I've been using that way for many many moons.
That is the fastest route, nothing else! Print it and go

I would agree as well. But...to be safe, take a look at the Minnesota department of transportation website and see about any possible road construction. Depending on what they are doing, it may or may not pay off to take an alternate route too... Just something to keep in mind before you go. May save a headache Steve
